.TH HSH 1 "November 2025" "Version 1.0" "Simple Shell Manual"

.SH NAME
hsh \- simple UNIX command line interpreter

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B hsh
.RI [ "command" " ..."]

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B hsh
is a simple UNIX command line interpreter that reads commands from standard input, parses them, and executes them.
It mimics basic functionalities of the standard shell \fBsh\fR.

The shell:
.IP • 2
Displays a prompt and waits for user input.
.IP • 2
Executes commands with arguments.
.IP • 2
Searches for executables in the PATH.
.IP • 2
Handles built-in commands such as \fBexit\fR and \fBenv\fR.
.IP • 2
Handles the "end of file" condition (Ctrl+D).

.SH BUILT-IN COMMANDS
.TP
.B exit [status]
Exit the shell with an optional exit status.
If no status is provided, the exit status of the last executed command is used.

.TP
.B env
Display the current environment variables.

.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Interactive mode:
.RS
.nf
$ ./hsh
$ ls -l
$ pwd
$ exit
.fi
.RE

.PP
Non-interactive mode:
.RS
.nf
$ echo "ls -l" | ./hsh
$ echo "/bin/pwd" | ./hsh
.fi
.RE

